    <div class="panel-group" id="accordion">
        <div class="faqHeader">Reviewers and Reviews</div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">What review types are eligible?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse in">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    "Past review uploads" is what we call it when a partnered journal sends us a large batch of review information in one go.  Where the submitting reviewer's email address matches a verified email address in our database we will invite that user to add the review to their profile.  If that user has selected "Automatically add reviews for partnered journals" we will add those reviews automatically without any confirmation from the user being required.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTen">How do open reviews appear on my Publons profile?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseTen" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Reviews submitted through Publons Transparent Review, as well as open reviews performed for other journals who operate open review policies, can be found on your Publons profile in the Peer review section. In both cases you must first claim the review to your Publons profile (either through a Reviewer Recognition integration, or by forwarding your review receipt). 
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseEleven">How do Publisher and Journal Review Permissions affect me?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseEleven" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    ome publishers require that you attain permission from the journal or the author before you make the content of your review public or sign your name to your review(s). You can see any journal's policy here. If you wish to make the content public or sign your name to a review for a journal that restricts you from doing so, please contact your editor. 
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faqHeader">Editors and Editor Records</div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo">What are Editor Records and who can add them?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseTwo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Editor records on Publons are a record of manuscripts that you have handled the peer review process for.  
                    This work includes finding and managing reviewers and contributing to the journal's decision regarding publication of the manuscript. 
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree">How are Editor Records verified?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseThree" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Handling Editor Records are verified by either forwarding editorial receipts to edits@publons.com or by administrators of partnered journals. 
                    Only verified handling editor records will be displayed on the detail pages of partnered journals. 
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFive">How do I invite reviewers to add their reviews to Publons?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseFive" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    Once you've added an editor record, you can invite the reviewers of that paper to add a record of the review to their Publons profile. 
                    To invite reviewers, click on the "Actions" column of the editor history page of your private dashboard.  We will email the reviewers, invite them to join Publons, and then add a record of the review to their profile. Reviewers who are recognised for their work are happy reviewers! 
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faqHeader">Publisher FAQs</div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseFour">How does it work for reviewers?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseFour" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    There are a number of ways reviews can be added to Publons:<br>
                    <strong>Researcher-added reviews </strong>- researchers can add a review record to their profile by forwarding their review receipt email to reviews@publons.com or filling out an online form.
                    <br> 
                    <strong>Journal integrations</strong> - For partner journals, reviewers can opt-in to Publons as part of the review submission process and the review data is transferred to Publons upon submission.  
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a class="accordion-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseSeven">What review information is made public?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseSeven" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    By default, the only review information displayed on a researcher's Publons profile is the name of the journal reviewed for and the number of reviews performed for each journal (please see example below). This is to ensure we protect reviewer anonymity and comply with journal review policies.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

